# Day 1 - Learning AI Beyond Just Passing Courses

Being a 3rd year student specializing in AI/ML, most of my learning till now revolved around passing exams, completing assignments, and studying course material.

But over time, studying these subjects actually made me curious about the deeper side of AI — the maths, logic, and real systems behind modern models.

Instead of only learning theory for grades, I now want to understand how things actually work under the hood.

Today I started exploring transformers and learned about self-attention mechanisms that help models understand relationships between words.

This repository will track my journey of learning AI more seriously, one small step every day.
